text:
<!channel> Here's the GEA calendar for the next few months. We'll have at least two additional events, but wanted to get this on everyone's radar so you can plan appropriately.

Friday October 6th: Guest Speaker - Chad Ingram, founder of <http://Distro.io|Distro.io>. 11-12:15 in W308 in the Tanner Building.

Wednesday October 11th: Growth Venture Connect, W410, 6-8pm

Friday October 20th: 1pm-2:30. Guest Speaker tbd, and alumni networking. Tanner Building. Room tbd. (optional lunch+networking from 12-1, must register online for this part)

Friday October 27th: Guest Speaker John Koelliker, founder of Leland. 11am-12:15 W308.

Friday November 3rd: BYU tech transfer office will speak and share how students can access and license technology. They're also bringing an alumni in who has used this tech to start a company. W308, 11-12:15

Friday November 17th: Guest Speaker Nathan Rich, founder of IsoTruss. 11-12:15 W308.
